Morningstar
CNN Money


HCSB Financial Corporation operates as the holding company for Horry County State Bank that provides commercial banking products and services primarily in the Horry County, South Carolina; and Columbus and Brunswick Counties, North Carolina. It offers a range of deposit services, including checking accounts, savings accounts, certificates of deposit, money market accounts, and individual retirement accounts. The company also originates real estate loans, including residential and commercial real estate loans, as well as construction and development loans; commercial loans comprising secured and unsecured loans, lines of credit, and working capital loans; consumer loans for personal and household purposes, such as secured and unsecured installment and term loans, home equity loans and lines of credit, and revolving lines of credit; and agricultural loans. In addition, it provides cash management services, sweep accounts, repurchase agreements, mobile banking services, remote deposit capture services, safe deposit boxes, travelers checks, direct deposit of payroll and social security checks, online banking services, and automatic drafts, as well as credit card services. The company operates through a network of eight branches. HCSB Financial Corporation was founded in 1987 and is based in Loris, South Carolina.


